- Opening Screen that allows users to choose between starting the game and the instructions
- If instructions is chosen, program will display how the game is played
- When game is started, tic tac toe screen appears
- Two players represented by the Xs and Os
- Players can take turn placing Xs and Os in the proper position
- The first player to complete a row, column, or diagonal earns one point
  - At any point during the game, the user will be able to restart or exit the game
  - To keep playing again, the user must reset the round
- The player who has gotten the most points is the winner; depending on which player wins the exit screen will appear differently
